react js props and state
=============================
1.props : props is a object which contains data to be transfered from parent 
          component to child component.
2.state : state contains data which is avaiable to all the functions with in
          the same component. when ever state changes, component will be re-rendered with upddated state data.

 note: props are immutable. This means that component can not change its own props. Porps are read-omjly and are passed down from paremt to child compoment


 React js hooks
 =================
 1.useState
 2.useEffect
 3.useContext (centralized data)

 Additiobal hooks
 -----------------
 4.useReducer (data management)
 5.useMemo
 6.useRef (forms)






